The paper presents a novel method for convex unconstrained optimization that applies to smooth objectives, non-smooth objectives, and stochastic optimization. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), optimization (cs.Optimization), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these, cs.LG and cs.Optimization are the most likely sub-categories, as the paper deals with optimization methods and their applicability to machine learning problems.
